<TITLE> Suicide bomb kills Afghan near US embassy </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 KABUL, Nov 27 (bdnews24.com/Reuters) - A suicide car bomber struck a convoy of foreign troops near the US embassy in Kabul on Thursday, killing one civilian and wounding six more, the head of the Afghan capital's police force said. The head of criminal investigations of Kabul police had said four civilians had been killed in the blast, but Kabul police chief Mohammad Ayoub Salangi said only one civilian had been killed and six more wounded when the bomber blew up his Toyota saloon car on a road near the embassy and the Health Ministry. US embassy staff were off work for the Thanksgiving public holiday and were unlikely to be out on the roads at the time, an embassy spokesman said. Spokesmen for international troops confirmed the blast, but were unable to provide any details
